aiTopic: Redefining workflows involving preprocessing and downstream analysis of variants in Illumina-sequenced ARTIC data for COVID-19 using multiple tools and filters.
This workflow takes a VCF dataset of variants and produces tabular lists of variants by samples and by variant, as well as an overview plot of variants and their allele frequencies.
Perform preprocessing, mapping, variant calling, annotation, and filtering of ARTIC ONT-sequenced COVID-19 data.
Perform paired end read mapping with bwa-mem followed by sensitive variant calling across a wide range of AFs with lofreq.
Perform single end read mapping with bowtie2 followed by sensitive variant calling across a wide range of AFs with lofreq.
Build a consensus sequence from FILTER PASS variants with intrasample allele-frequency above a configurable consensus threshold, hard-masking regions with low coverage and ambiguous sites.
Annotate variants in ampliconic SARS-CoV-2 Illumina sequencing data, classify samples with pangolin and nextclade, and generate quality control reports.
Download fastq files for sequencing run accessions provided in a text file using fasterq-dump, creating one job per listed run accession.
Load the nf-core/rnaseq Nextflow config file with default parameters and options for all environments.

Configure the nf-core/methylseq Nextflow pipeline with default options, including specifying pipeline version, container, output directory, and pipeline options, and defining profiles for different environments.

Customize default config options for all environments in the nf-core/methylseq Nextflow workflow by setting various flags, params, and container settings, and load custom profiles and configs, while capturing exit codes and creating timeline, report, trace, and DAG files.

Prepare data for variant calling analysis by aligning to reference genome and performing data cleanup operations to correct technical biases, using the BROAD Best Practice Data Pre-processing Workflow 4.1.0.0.
Run the U of Michigan variant caller workflow for the TOPMed Freeze 3a variant calling pipeline, including steps to calculate DNA contamination, create CRAM index files, and perform variant calling.
Convert multiple VCF files into GDS files, attempt to give unique variant IDs, and optionally check the GDS files against their supposed VCF inputs.

Calculate linkage disequilibrium on a set of GDS files, prune variants based on specified parameters, subset GDS files based on a vector of variants, merge the subsetted GDS files into one, and check the merged GDS file against its inputs.
Create a null model from phenotype data with the GENESIS biostatistical package, run association tests on genetic data, and summarize the results.
Calculate the read length and coverage for each input BAM or CRAM file, and generate a report summarizing the results.
Process 10x genomics sequencing data by correcting cell barcodes and UMIs, aligning reads, marking duplicates, and generating output files in various formats, based on the v2 chemistry.
Concatenate multiple files, capture version and analysis date, and output the concatenated files.
Convert BAM file to unmapped BAMs by first reverting the SAM files and then sorting the unmapped BAMs.
Aggregate and analyze state government tax collections data, using different tax categories and creating interactive maps.
Run the PCAWG Sanger variant calling workflow with input tumor and normal BAM files and reference data files using CWL tool or Dockstore CLI.
Sort input files based on specified key positions using the BAMStats tool with a Docker container.
